column82:
The main clinical and MRI-based endpoints are:
- Annualized confirmed relapse rate (ARR; based on the
number of confirmed relapses per subject-year);
- Time from core study randomization to first confirmed
relapse;
- Time from core baseline to first 12-week confirmed
disability accumulation (CDA);
- Time from core baseline to first 24-week confirmed
disability accumulation (CDA);
- Percent change from baseline in brain volume (PCBV) at
all assessments;
- Cumulative number of combined unique active lesions
(CUAL, defined as new Gd+ T1 lesions plus new or
enlarging T2 lesions without double-counting the lesions)
at all assessments.
